{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsQs7G1VNGpKhamAbZUz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ETL job completed successfully after the memory fix.\n\n**Summary:**\n\n1. **Failure identified**: `etl-job` was `Failed` (BackoffLimitExceeded) with error:\n   `[INVALID_DRIVER_MEMORY] System memory 259522560 must be at least 471859200` — the 256m heap was insufficient for Spark's minimum requirement.\n\n2. **Root cause diagnosed**: Diagnostic server and `skew_info.txt` confirmed `user_id=999` holds 50,000 of 100,000 records (**skew_ratio=500x**, far above the 10x threshold), driving Stage 3's `GROUP BY user_id` to blow past the tiny 256m heap.\n\n3. **Fix applied**: Reconstructed `etl-job.yaml` (not present in this environment's filesystem, same as the prior stage) at `/workspace/cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml`, raising `--driver-memory` and `spark.executor.memory` from `256m` → `1g`, and additionally enabled `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true` / `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true` to address the underlying skew. Deleted the failed job and reapplied.\n\n4. **Verified**: `etl-job` is now `Complete (1/1)`, ran in 92s, log ends with `spark_etl_pipeline_verified`.\n\nNote: I checked the `spark-worker` deployment per the task's warning about an external process changing replica count — it's steady at 1/1 — but this job runs in `local[2]` mode inside its own driver pod, so worker replica count doesn't actually factor into this job's execution; the memory fix alone resolved it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3467,"cache_read_input_tokens":69952,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3467},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0921cad7-